"{\"uid\": \"horseandhound.co.uk-news-olympic-eventing-dressage-results-british-team-paris-laura-collett-865707\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"It's been a packed schedule ofOlympic eventingdressage in Paris, with every single competitor crammed into nine hours of quick-fire tests, so here's a round-up of all the top stories.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 58, \"end\": 63, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4297753258337294e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The day may have been soggy and cold in France, but there were some fabulous, record-breaking highlights to brighten the gloom and warm the cockles before the sun returns tomorrow for cross-country day.\", \"from\": 184, \"to\": 386, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 230, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9990704533851238, \"rank\": 0.0009264068565361998, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laura Collettproduced a scintillating test to smash the Olympic eventing dressage test record and take the lead.\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain hold a 7.4pen lead over Germany, thanks to three tests in the top 11.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 581, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 504, \"end\": 511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999189839455291, \"rank\": 8.10225717670818e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 536, \"end\": 543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.8966616086251434, \"rank\": 0.11254427140725107, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Michael Jung was just a fraction behind on Chipmunk FRH to boost Germany's bid for gold.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 585, \"end\": 597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\", \"score\": 0.9988531015029164, \"rank\": 0.0011482035875302495, \"text\": \"Michael Jung\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_E._Jung\"}, {\"begin\": 628, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alvin_and_the_Chipmunks\", \"score\": 0.9861492844595021, \"rank\": 0.01404524860900251, \"text\": \"Chipmunk\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alvin_and_the_Chipmunks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alvin_and_the_Chipmunks\"}, {\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.8966616086251434, \"rank\": 0.11254427140725107, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Hua Tianimpressed as the only individual rider to feature in the top 20, taking third spot for China.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9999993196058808, \"rank\": 6.705227510561159e-07, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 775, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9905275328338551, \"rank\": 0.009532915836308619, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reigning European champion and Britain's anchormanRos Canteris currently in sixth, cementing Britain's place at the top of the teams.\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"score\": 0.5889700555958167, \"rank\": 0.6978789258075736, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Figure_Skating_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999189839455291, \"rank\": 8.10225717670818e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999189839455291, \"rank\": 8.10225717670818e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom McEwenwas the British pathfinder, and produced a solid test for 11th at the end of the day.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.99995549368668, \"rank\": 2.3325546205804206e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Frenchman St\\u00e9phane Landois was best of the home side in seventh with Chaman Dumontceau  Seven-time OlympianKarin Donckersdelivered a personal best for Belgium, lying 13th.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999981669051042, \"rank\": 1.8329377925207676e-06, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"German'sJulia Krajewskiwas first into the ring on Nickel 21, and 15th in the final dressage reckoning.\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Liz Hallidaywas a late call-up to the US team, but performed best of the trio with a top-20 score.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999761374726575, \"rank\": 0.00022981210940361272, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't just the stars in the limelight.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the youngest riders in the field, 25-year-old Robin Godel, posted a sub-30 mark.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, one horse bit his tongue, causing the rider to be eliminated, although the horse was not seriously injured when checked by a vet.\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1672, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An Ecuadorian horse and his rider with a combined age of 78 had their turn in the Versailles arena.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A student rider managing to combine top-level eventing with an engineering degree made her Olympic debut.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shane Rosefranked his remarkable return to top sport after a career-threatening injury in March.\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1978, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A mare with a fear of horses was full of confidence in the atmospheric arena.\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the joint-youngest horse in the competition is making his rider very excited for the future.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2155, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Riders are unanimous that Pierre Le Goupil's cross-country track is beautifully crafted, but their opinions vary.\", \"from\": 2157, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Goupil_&_Cie\", \"score\": 0.9935874826063947, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Goupil\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Goupil_&_Cie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Goupil_&_Cie\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The course is not only stunning, but is inspired by many historic and cultural French themes.\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2365, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2351, \"end\": 2357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7748481961478504, \"rank\": 0.2561911267349609, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sunday's action kicks off at 10.30am local time (9.30 British time).\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2435, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2421, \"end\": 2428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.99995549368668, \"rank\": 2.3325546205804206e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And finally, to help you to prepare, we have rounded up thefive things you will not want to missduring Sunday's action.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You might also b